FBIS3-48078 "dreas015_c_94008" FBIS-EAS-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 North Korea South Daily Cited on `Violation of Human Rights' SK1901133894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1021 GMT 19 Jan 94 SK1901133894 Pyongyang KCNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- Jun Sik, chairman of the Human Rights Committee of the National Alliance for Democracy and Reunification (Chongukyonhap) of South Korea, at a press conference urged the authorities to stop the violation of human rights, the South Korean newspaper HANGYORE SHINMUN reported. Noting that such human rights abuses as in the years of military fascist dictatorship continued under the Kim Yong-sam regime, he said: "All manner of harsh treatment such as torture and severe penalties must be totally checked."
